<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 5000, 9000 Series Without Lowered heater Box - REMOVE AND INSTALL - BLOWER
        MOTOR ASSEMBLIES
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1601507" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>BLOWER MOTOR ASSEMBLIES</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the key and blower motor switch is OFF, or the battery ground strap has been
                    disconnected.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the screws securing the passenger seat and the Blend-Air housing cover plate.
                    Remove the seat and cover from the cab.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the passenger side scuff plate and the blower motor access panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the blower motor wiring connector and ground wire.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the motor cooling air hose (vent) from the blower housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601518">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1601518" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1601506D.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Blower Assembly Exploded View</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. BLEND-AIR UNIT HOUSING</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. BLOWER HOUSING</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. BLOWER RESISTORS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. VENT HOSES</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. BLOWER MOTOR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the mounting screws and the blower motor assembly from the blower housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To separate the fan from the motor, remove the fan lock nuts and lift the fan and spacer
                    from the motor shaft.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the fan on the motor shaft as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Position the metal spacer on the shaft.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Position the fan on the motor shaft.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the fan lock nut and tighten to 1 to 1.25 lbf-ft (1 to 1.7 Nm).</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the blower motor assembly in the blower housing and install the mounting screws
                    (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601518">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the motor cooling air hose (vent) to the outlet on the blower housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the blower wiring connector and ground wire.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect battery if disconnected.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the blower motor operation.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the passenger side scuff plate and the blower motor access panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the Blend-Air unit cover and the passenger seat.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
